description:
Role Summary:

With the aim to diversify our business, our management is actively developing opportunities in other business sectors. 

To copy with our growth, we are looking for a high caliber candidate for the position of Assistant Manager, Marketing and Research Analytics.

Responsibilities:

Responsible for all-round market research across different potential industries including data collection, figures analysis and market trend forecast;
Conduct in-depth analysis covering business models, customers’ preferences and needs, branding and risk assessment;
Provide regular market intelligence and competitors analysis for strategic planning and decision making;
Prepare periodical reports in sales performance analysis, budgeting, costing and forecasting;
Perform ad-hoc tasks as required.

 Requirements:

Degree holder in Business Administration, Marketing, Finance or related discipline;
Minimum 5 years of experience in market research and data analysis;
Knowledge and experience in merger & acquisition, franchise, emerging business is highly preferred;
Strong business sense, analytical, detail-oriented and self-initiative;
Enthusiastic, sensitive in market changes and future trends, able to use initiative to come up with new ideas;
Good command of spoken and written English, Cantonese and Putonghua;
Able to travel when required.

Key Responsibilities

Provide editorial and event management support in all publicity related assignments;
Support the department in English and Chinese editorial needs, including corporate materials and marketing write-ups;
Act as key liaison between external stakeholders and internal departments to ensure communication objective are met;
Supervise the team in day-to-day assignments and manage departmental calendar effectively;
Support building digital capability across the enterprise and act as custodian of all online assets;
Research and collect information on industry and public affairs to keep the company abreast of market developments;
Assist in ad-hoc projects as assigned.

Requirement

Bachelor Degree holder, preferably in Translations, English Studies, Mass Communications or related disciplines;
Minimum 10 years of solid experience in media, corporate communications, public affairs, or research and analysis, preferably in sizable company or news outlet;
At least 2 years’ experience in supervisory role in reputable organization is preferred;
Excellent command of written and spoken English and Chinese, conversant in Mandarin is preferred;
Strong PC skills, familiar with creative software is preferable;
Must have solid media experience and proven track record in handling large scale events;
Good interpersonal and communications skills; team player and meticulous;
Candidate with lesser experience will be considered for an Assistant Manager position.

We offer long-term career prospect and competitive remuneration package to the appointed candidate. Please apply in confidence with your detailed resume stating your current and expected salary to Group Human Resources Department

by email to recruit(at)shuntakgroup.com

or mail to Penthouse 39/F, West Tower, Shun Tak Centre, 200 Connaught Road Central, Hong Kong

(Please quote reference number and applied position)

The information supplied by the applicants will be used in accordance with the Personal Data (Privacy) Policy of Shun Tak Group (a copy of which will be provided upon request). Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.


www.shuntakgroup.com

Job Description


Copywriting for NUU Mobile will lead the strategic storytelling responsibility in creating original, culturally vibrant, brand engagement: from top level campaign concepts, to arrange media advertising, and everything in between.
Play an instrumental role in shaping the expression of the NUU Mobile brand.
Bring ideas to life and convey our marketing messages to our target audiences.
Execute and shepherd concepts from conception and executive buy-in through all stages of creative development, production and post-production—ensuring faithful execution, quality, and brand consistency all the way.
Seek to push the brand and our marketing practice into new media, experimenting, testing and tracking.
Qualifications

Degree in Fine Arts, Communication Design, Advertising or equivalent practical experience.
5+ years of writing and creative direction experience at a creative agency;
Exceptional conceptual and written storytelling talent;
Proven experience developing strategically grounded, creative ideas across digital and traditional media, for major consumer brands;
A strong and diverse portfolio of original advertising and brand engagement work, including digital, video, and new media;
Expert understanding of creative considerations across print, website, mobile, online advertising, social media, video, and so on;
Ability to thoughtfully and persuasively articulate creative concepts to cross-functional teams;
Proficiency in creative and productivity applications: Photoshop, InDesign, Keynote/PowerPoint/Google Slides;
Experience in technology, consumer technology or consumer lifestyle categories;
Travelling is required and will stay in USA at least 6 months per year.

What You Will Be Doing:

Help develop marketing strategies and creative ideas;
Manage social media projects (channel include but are not limited to Facebook, Instagram, YouTube and TikTok)
Work closely with vendors / internal teams to ideate, plan and execute digital marketing campaign projects;
Communicate closely with clients, identify and solve problems with professional solutions;
Conduct market research, develop content plan and create social media content.

 What You Need for this Position:

Degree or above in Business, Advertising, Communication, Marketing, Journalism, Media, project management or related disciplines;
Fluent in both written and spoken English, Mandarin and Cantonese;
Excellent communication, interpersonal and negotiation skills is a must;
Passionate and have good knowledge in social media and new media;
Great marketing sense, multi-tasking and time management;
Willing to take challenges and attention to details;
Proficient in MS office application
Experience in project management and strategic marketing, preferably in managing social media projects and creative campaigns is a plus;
Being capable of creating visual content is a plus;
International exposure/ experience in China is definitely an advantage

 Benefits We Offer:

 5 days’ work
Quarterly Performance Bonus
Medical Coverage including Dental
Flexible Working Hours
Overtime Meal and Transportation allowance
Birthday, Wedding, Graduation and other special leaves
Fun, young and joyful environment 

 Be a GURU, be our next great hire. APPLY NOW!

*All information will be treated as confidential and used solely for recruitment purposes.
